# source: http://ranger.nongnu.org/
# ranger is a console file manager with VI key bindings. It provides a minimalistic and nice curses interface with a view on the directory hierarchy. It ships with "rifle", a file launcher that is good at automatically finding out which program to use for what file type.

# source: https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/ranger
#  ranger - visual file manager

# To copy the default configuration to this directory issue the following command ~/.config/ranger
ranger --copy-config=all

#  |2.2.3|   hyenatop2 in ~/dev/bossjones/bossjones-dotfiles
